		<profileDesc>
			<abstract>
				<p>There is currently considerable interest in developing general non-linear density models based on latent, or hidden, variables. Such models have the ability to discover the presence of a relatively small number of underlying &apos;causes&apos; which, acting in combination, give rise to the apparent complexity of the observed data set. Unfortunately , to train such models generally requires large computational effort. In this paper we introduce a novel latent variable algorithm which retains the general non-linear capabilities of previous models but which uses a training procedure based on the EM algorithm. We demonstrate the performance of the model on a toy problem and on data from flow diagnostics for a multi-phase oil pipeline.</p>
			</abstract>
